<bigifyExample="This is an example of the bigify layout, which is essentially a grid of same size items taken from the specified source, along with one large item with a size defined as a multiple of regular items. The grid is defined by rows and columns. The size of the large item is set in terms of rows and columns that must be less than or equal to the grid dimensions. When you select an item, it becomes the big item and the other items are shuffled to fit around it, maintaining their order.

The bigify panel has two members, item, which provides the attributes applied to every normal size grid element; and bigItem, which provides attributes applied to the big item.

